-- ‘Lone Ranger’ Collects $9.86 Million in July 4 U.S. Sales
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   P a l m e r i
-- 2013-07-05T16:08:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-05/-lone-ranger-collects-9-86-million-in-july-4-u-s-sales.html
Walt Disney Co. (DIS) ’s “The Lone Ranger”
took in $9.86 million in July 4 sales in U.S. and Canadian
theaters, bringing its two-day total to $19.5 million,
Hollywood.com reported.  The $225 million film featuring Johnny Depp was trailing
Universal Pictures’ “Despicable Me 2,” which collected $34.3
million in its opening day, according to data from
 Hollywood.com .  To contact the reporter on this story:
